<br />

<br />
That's an interesting viewpoint, but I know a lot of people who use CoTAM, and the enchanter spell CoD.  They are very valuable tools in certain raid settings, and can significantly increase your kill raid in group settings (a la LDoN).
<br />

<br />
I would highly recommend that if you have CoTAM, that you get Elemental Silence as well.  The two absolutly go hand in hand.  When you select your charm target, mez it first, then apply your strongest debuff (Malosinia).  This will help with your charm durations.
<br />

<br />
*EDIT*.  Sorry, the rant kind of distracted me I guess.  You are already doing the mezz/debuff.  Charm is very much subject to the EQ Random Number Generator.  I've had it break 5 times in 5 minutes, then have it last for 20 minutes on the next recharm.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://scrubfire.dyndns.org/KJ_Sig.jpg" border="0" />
