			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have used Charm alot in Takish adventures, one thing I find makes a major diffrence is to debuff the mob before charming.
<br />

<br />
I find sometimes charm will break almost as soon as mez wears off and it can wear off after just a few seconds several times in a row but I find once charm sticks a certain length of time its lasts a good while. 
<br />

<br />
You also need to have a very good and friendly healer, most of the time im with guild mates so I know I can trust them to heal me when charm breaks but I have had times when I let my group kill my pet because the healer just wasent up to the job.
<br />

<br />
My usual tactic is once I have a mob charmed is to shrink it and park it on the other side of the room then back my self into the corner furthest from the fighting and pet.
<br />

<br />
If I miss the charm breaking and get attacked I can normally channel a mez on the 2nd or 3rd attempt  at which point and im down to about 70% health and am able to re debuff and charm the mob again.
<br />

<br />
The sad fact is that Takish is the only place I have CoTAM of any real practical use, its possible to use charm in BoT but not the same reliability and often its just a pain.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
